name: Chewing Gum
overview: The life of Tracey, a religious, Beyoncé-obsessed 22-year-old  living in an estate in Tower Hamlets, and the mishaps of her neighbourhood, friends and family. Oh, and obvs her boyfriend!

episodes.name: Sex & Violence
episodes.overview: Tracey plans to go all the way with her reluctant and devout fiancé Ronald, until she bumps into charming estate poet Connor

episodes.name: Binned
episodes.overview: Tracey's first sexual encounter leaves her panicked about pregnancy. She also needs to bin Ronald as she is determined to make Connor her new boyfriend.

episodes.name: Possession
episodes.overview: Tracey takes the chance to improve her future and heads off to a recruitment day, while her devil-fearing sister Cynthia covers her shift in the shop

episodes.name: The Unicorn
episodes.overview: Connor's having trouble in the bedroom. Tracey decides a threesome is the next step. Cynthia's internet searches take her to some eye-opening places.

episodes.name: The Last Supper
episodes.overview: Tracey's cousin Boy Tracy pays a visit and surprises in more ways than one. Connor's foray into the world of performance poetry doesn't go well.

episodes.name: Tolled Road
episodes.overview: Connor wants Tracey to move in with him, but she's busy trying to stop her sister from marrying her gay ex-fiancé Ronald

episodes.name: WTF Happened?
episodes.overview: Tracey returns to the Pensbourne Estate but she's rejected by both Candice and Joy, and things aren't as easy as she would like.

episodes.name: Replacements
episodes.overview: Tracey's mum sets her some challenging tests before she can move back into the family home, meantime Tracey is busy replacing Connor and Candice.

episodes.name: I Just Need Some Company
episodes.overview: Tracey's confidence is wobbly. She wants some male company - someone who thinks she's attractive - and cousin Boy Tracy has a plan.

episodes.name: Orlando
episodes.overview: Tracey finds a four legged friend, while Mandy makes Esther an online dating profile that sees her assume a new identity.
